1
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:19,811
[Joe] Previously on You:

2
00:00:19,894 --> 00:00:20,979
I still believe...

3
00:00:21,062 --> 00:00:23,023
-You okay there, Joe?
-...in The One.

4
00:00:23,106 --> 00:00:26,776
I'm married but to the wrong person.
What if you're the right one?

5
00:00:26,860 --> 00:00:29,237
[Marienne] Juliette told Ryan
that we spent the day together.

6
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:30,822
Now he's threatening me.

7
00:00:30,905 --> 00:00:31,948
Stay away from her.

8
00:00:32,032 --> 00:00:35,702
[Joe] As long as he's in the picture,
you are always going to lose.

9
00:00:38,496 --> 00:00:40,749
How much do you know
about Love's first husband?

10
00:00:40,832 --> 00:00:44,753
Love has no loyalty
for anyone but herself.

11
00:00:44,836 --> 00:00:47,380
[Theo]
And you've been buried in here, obsessed!

12
00:00:47,464 --> 00:00:49,466
Just move on, okay? She's dead!

13
00:00:49,549 --> 00:00:51,593
Get the fuck out now!

14
00:00:52,302 --> 00:00:54,095
Do you and Joe wanna play
with me and Cary?

15
00:00:54,179 --> 00:00:56,514
-I killed Natalie for you!
-Shut up.

16
00:00:56,598 --> 00:00:57,724
Go.

17
00:01:03,521 --> 00:01:04,481
Fuck this.

18
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:07,525
-[Sherry] What are you doing?
-Stand back!

19
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:11,196
You just shot my ear.

20
00:01:13,448 --> 00:01:16,951
She caught her husband cheating
with your stepmom and she murdered her!

21
00:01:17,035 --> 00:01:18,828
Get us out of here, Theo.

22
00:01:30,215 --> 00:01:31,633
[Joe] Shirley Jackson wrote

23
00:01:31,716 --> 00:01:35,595
that suburbia
is where people start to come apart.

24
00:01:36,596 --> 00:01:39,766
I thought I'd escape before
that happened to me, but if I'd done that,

25
00:01:40,391 --> 00:01:42,435
I'd never have met you.

26
00:01:44,395 --> 00:01:45,814
I'm not free...

27
00:01:45,897 --> 00:01:47,941
unless we both are, Marienne.

28
00:01:48,024 --> 00:01:51,986
So I had to. You deserve a man
who does what has to be done.

29
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:58,493
Right now, I have to save my son
from his mother.

30
00:02:00,453 --> 00:02:04,415
Mr. Mooney used to say
there's a monster inside every boy,

31
00:02:04,499 --> 00:02:06,584
all too easy to feed.

32
00:02:06,668 --> 00:02:10,296
If you make it strong, it will take over.

33
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:12,465
We can save Henry together.

34
00:02:12,549 --> 00:02:15,260
I just need to get us out

35
00:02:15,343 --> 00:02:18,680
before Love feeds Henry so much
as another bite.

36
00:02:24,936 --> 00:02:26,813
They're saying she moved to Ohio.

37
00:02:26,896 --> 00:02:30,316
Yeah, sure. She left her plants
and the picture of her mom.

38
00:02:31,401 --> 00:02:33,111
It was her boyfriend.

39
00:02:33,194 --> 00:02:36,197
-No. Or maybe she ran away.
-I could've stopped him.

40
00:02:36,739 --> 00:02:41,119
-The last time it ruined my entire life.
-You mean, like, with your mom...?

41
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:43,413
It made her hate me so much,
she put me here.

42
00:02:44,289 --> 00:02:47,542
So I thought, with Fiona,
I didn't want her to hate me.

43
00:02:47,625 --> 00:02:51,296
For the record, you don't know
how your mom feels. You're making it up.

44
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:54,174
Hey, trust me, I do it too.

45
00:02:54,257 --> 00:02:58,178
But I'll never actually know
why mine left me here.

46
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:01,389
Neither will you.

47
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:07,061
[suspenseful music playing]

48
00:03:40,386 --> 00:03:41,471
[phone buzzing]

49
00:03:44,307 --> 00:03:45,683
[door unlocks, then opens]

50
00:03:46,309 --> 00:03:47,810
-[Love] Joe?
-[door closes]

51
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:48,728
I'm home.

52
00:03:49,437 --> 00:03:52,315
[Joe] Fuck. If she sees blood, it's over.

53
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:54,609
Joe?

54
00:03:59,364 --> 00:04:01,032
What are you doing in here?

55
00:04:01,115 --> 00:04:03,576
Looking for a charger. That's the one.

56
00:04:08,414 --> 00:04:11,000
[groans] What a fucking day.

57
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:14,295
We need to figure out
how we're gonna endgame the Conrads.

58
00:04:14,379 --> 00:04:16,756
-Brainstorm...
-[Joe] Something is up with her.

59
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:19,050
Also, we need to have an alibi.

60
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:22,595
-So I did get an Airbnb in Mill Valley.
-[Joe] She's barely looking at me.

61
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:25,765
Sherry and Cary aren't enough
to throw her this off-balance.

62
00:04:25,848 --> 00:04:27,850
And the bakery, I have an order.

63
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:31,437
It's a big one, so that'll be good
to keep everything open.

64
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:33,398
And I had a thought about us.

65
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,275
Is this...

66
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:38,027
Conrad blood?

67
00:04:40,697 --> 00:04:44,409
-No, that's Theo. He came by the bakery.
-[Joe] Oh, no.

68
00:04:44,492 --> 00:04:46,035
I, uh... He--

69
00:04:46,119 --> 00:04:48,955
Um, I had to...

70
00:04:49,038 --> 00:04:50,999
[Joe] That's what she can't look at.

71
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:52,417
Poor Theo.

72
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:55,461
He's still there, in the basement.

73
00:04:56,421 --> 00:04:59,632
[Joe] Fuck. Okay, problem or opportunity?

74
00:04:59,716 --> 00:05:02,260
I'll handle him.
Don't give it another thought.

75
00:05:02,343 --> 00:05:03,303
My epiphany.

76
00:05:03,928 --> 00:05:05,513
I was just thinking,

77
00:05:05,596 --> 00:05:09,475
like, we're gonna be through this
so soon, right?

78
00:05:09,559 --> 00:05:10,601
[Joe] I hope.

79
00:05:10,685 --> 00:05:11,728
-Right?
-Yeah.

80
00:05:11,811 --> 00:05:16,065
I just think it's perfect, so--
To really fucking start a new chapter.

81
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:19,736
It's time for us
to try for another baby, Joe.

82
00:05:20,528 --> 00:05:21,362
[Joe] I'm...

83
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:23,990
actually speechless.

84
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:30,371
I want nothing more in the world, Love.

85
00:05:32,123 --> 00:05:33,499
Yeah, let's do it.

86
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:42,133
Too bad, tomorrow,
Henry and I will be gone.

87
00:05:42,216 --> 00:05:46,054
Of course, this all hinges
on the only question that matters.

88
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:49,307
When I go...

89
00:05:50,892 --> 00:05:52,310
will you come with me?

90
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:16,918
I'm sorry.

91
00:06:17,502 --> 00:06:21,047
Theo, hi, it's me.
Can you call me and check in, please?

92
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:28,054
I was too harsh when I kicked you out...

93
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:30,890
but you don't have to--

94
00:06:32,975 --> 00:06:36,020
-[door opens]
-Just let me know you're okay, please.

95
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:46,072
[Joe] You poor, dumb kid.

96
00:06:46,697 --> 00:06:47,949
I'm so sorry.

97
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:58,501
-Come on, man.
-He's not coming back.

98
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:01,212
It's been hours.

99
00:07:02,463 --> 00:07:03,714
Hey, let me see that.

100
00:07:05,758 --> 00:07:07,009
No.

101
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:11,222
Sher, I took a survival medicine seminar
with a dude who won Season 6 of Alone.

102
00:07:11,305 --> 00:07:14,434
I can't hear you...

103
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:17,645
because you shot me in the ear.

104
00:07:17,728 --> 00:07:18,855
It ricocheted.

105
00:07:18,938 --> 00:07:21,566
Tell that to the part of my ear
plastered to that bucket.

106
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:25,153
-Red flag, okay? This is my turn.
-No. No more techniques.

107
00:07:25,236 --> 00:07:27,864
[Joe] Love's right.
They are gonna argue to death.

108
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:29,866
Marriage brings out the worst in us all.

109
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:33,369
-That's not fair. Just let me--
-Don't! You've done enough.

110
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:37,415
-You're... You're hysterical.
-Fuck you! That is sexist as shit!

111
00:07:37,498 --> 00:07:39,500
I am a feminist...

112
00:07:40,334 --> 00:07:41,586
who grazed you!

113
00:07:41,669 --> 00:07:44,797
Oh, you wanna know
what grazing feels like?

114
00:07:45,590 --> 00:07:47,758
-Hey, hey!
-Don't get hysterical.

115
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:49,594
-I took a seminar.
-Hey, hey!

116
00:07:51,429 --> 00:07:53,764
[Joe] Oh, fuck. I'm gonna need more tarps.

117
00:07:54,348 --> 00:07:56,601
No! [groans]

118
00:07:56,684 --> 00:07:58,394
Oh, my God.

119
00:08:00,188 --> 00:08:02,231
-Cary?
-You didn't graze me.

120
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:05,067
You fucking...

121
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:08,905
shot me in the leg.

122
00:08:13,701 --> 00:08:15,077
[phone buzzing]

123
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:22,835
-Hey, I've been trying to reach you.
-[Marienne] Um, Joe...

124
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:26,005
Ryan's dead.

125
00:08:26,088 --> 00:08:28,174
-What?
-Mugging, apparently.

126
00:08:28,257 --> 00:08:30,635
Been a few in the area. Guy with a knife.

127
00:08:30,718 --> 00:08:35,264
Seems like this just went really bad,
but the police still interrogated me.

128
00:08:36,098 --> 00:08:38,226
I feel like this is gonna blow back on me.

129
00:08:38,309 --> 00:08:40,978
-I just know it.
-This was part of a string of muggings?

130
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:43,481
Yeah, but that doesn't mean anything.

131
00:08:43,564 --> 00:08:48,027
-Weren't you with Juliette last night?
-Yes, I was. I have an alibi, but...

132
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:51,906
I also have a very long history
of being fucked by the system.

133
00:08:51,989 --> 00:08:54,116
A system that was made by and for Ryan.

134
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,743
Can I disagree?

135
00:08:55,826 --> 00:08:58,246
Not about the system
but just about this moment.

136
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:03,543
I'd love to be wrong.

137
00:09:03,626 --> 00:09:06,671
Listen, the man who hurt you,

138
00:09:06,754 --> 00:09:10,716
who wanted to steal your child...

139
00:09:12,218 --> 00:09:14,428
he is now gone forever.

140
00:09:15,429 --> 00:09:17,723
You shouldn't send the mugger flowers,

141
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:20,643
but I am saying
this is your life getting easier.

142
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:25,189
-Promise not to judge?
-No, never.

143
00:09:26,357 --> 00:09:27,858
I'm glad he's dead.

144
00:09:32,488 --> 00:09:36,117
Can I tell you something else
that happened last night?

145
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:39,954
Love and I are officially separating.

146
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:42,582
Wait, seriously?

147
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:47,044
But, like, no, I'm-- I'm so--
I'm so sorry.

148
00:09:47,128 --> 00:09:47,962
Don't be.

149
00:09:48,045 --> 00:09:51,340
We're both gonna be free... very soon.

150
00:09:53,050 --> 00:09:56,804
Why don't you get out of town
while this Ryan drama dies down?

151
00:09:56,887 --> 00:10:00,600
-Yeah, we should.
-Just think of some place you wanna go.

152
00:10:00,683 --> 00:10:02,560
Anywhere. And just go.

153
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:05,521
Hey, Joe.

154
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:10,151
Come with us.

155
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:17,325
I know, I know, that's crazy.

156
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:19,035
No, it's not, it's not.

157
00:10:19,118 --> 00:10:23,289
You've been such a rock,
and I let myself fantasize about a...

158
00:10:24,206 --> 00:10:27,418
About a simple, happy, healthy family
for a second, and when I...

159
00:10:28,169 --> 00:10:31,589
When I picture that, I picture you.
And Henry, of course.

160
00:10:31,672 --> 00:10:33,883
And I know you said you love me,

161
00:10:33,966 --> 00:10:36,677
but it was in a certain moment,
I get that,

162
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:39,263
but I realized, I actually, um...

163
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:43,351
I love you.

164
00:10:43,976 --> 00:10:45,353
I love you, and...

165
00:10:46,312 --> 00:10:48,230
Yeah, so that.

166
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:54,695
That's probably way too much, too soon.

167
00:10:54,779 --> 00:10:55,655
No.

168
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:56,947
Marienne.

169
00:10:57,907 --> 00:10:58,949
Yes!

170
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:00,993
Yes. Count us in.

171
00:11:01,077 --> 00:11:05,206
We'd be crazy not to try after everything
we've been through to get here, right?

172
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:07,667
We just have to tie up a few loose ends.

173
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:10,503
I can't believe we're doing this.

174
00:11:11,837 --> 00:11:13,881
I can. It's fate.

175
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:17,009
Mm. Gotta go.

176
00:11:17,093 --> 00:11:21,138
Bunch of songbirds just landed on me
and I think we're going flying.

177
00:11:21,222 --> 00:11:23,224
[both laughing]

178
00:11:25,476 --> 00:11:27,019
I'll see you in the sky.

179
00:11:36,404 --> 00:11:39,824
You invited me, we have a future.

180
00:11:40,449 --> 00:11:44,995
This will be the last ugly thing
I ever have to do.

181
00:11:47,498 --> 00:11:48,833
[Theo groaning]

182
00:11:51,711 --> 00:11:53,295
Come on.

183
00:11:56,966 --> 00:12:00,219
Love couldn't even finish the job.
So much for a clean break.

184
00:12:00,302 --> 00:12:02,722
The kid knows everything. If he talks...

185
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:05,975
[groaning]

186
00:12:08,477 --> 00:12:11,147
Finish it. No one would know.

187
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:12,773
I'm sorry.

188
00:12:13,983 --> 00:12:16,068
I'm so, so sorry.

189
00:12:16,152 --> 00:12:17,111
[Joe] I would know.

190
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:20,030
Didn't I just promise the love of my life

191
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:23,117
a happy, healthy, new beginning?

192
00:12:26,454 --> 00:12:28,038
I will never...

193
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:31,459
touch her again.

194
00:12:32,251 --> 00:12:34,879
You think
this is because you kissed my wife?

195
00:12:34,962 --> 00:12:36,172
It was once.

196
00:12:38,257 --> 00:12:40,259
Oh, you fucked my wife?

197
00:12:40,342 --> 00:12:43,304
What a mess my wife has made.

198
00:12:45,055 --> 00:12:46,557
I loved her.

199
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:51,979
Why did she do this?

200
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:56,066
This is not your fault. She fooled me too.

201
00:12:57,026 --> 00:12:58,402
Are you gonna...

202
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,154
kill me?

203
00:13:04,366 --> 00:13:05,785
[Theo groaning]

204
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:16,629
[Joe] There is a hospital 20 minutes away.
My escape window is closing.

205
00:13:16,712 --> 00:13:20,341
I gotta keep this kid
from blabbing the second he's admitted.

206
00:13:41,445 --> 00:13:42,404
Okay, Theo,

207
00:13:43,322 --> 00:13:46,659
I'm going to give you a little nap,
all right?

208
00:13:46,742 --> 00:13:49,411
Cary Conrad uses this stuff all the time.

209
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:52,248
So it shouldn't exacerbate
your head injury.

210
00:13:52,331 --> 00:13:53,290
Too much.

211
00:14:01,674 --> 00:14:02,633
Julie.

212
00:14:04,677 --> 00:14:05,803
Julia.

213
00:14:05,886 --> 00:14:07,972
Julia Quinn-Goldberg.

214
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:52,141
-Who do you think it was?
-Word on the street is mugging.

215
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:54,560
-[Andrew] "The street"? Name your source.
-I saw a tweet.

216
00:14:54,643 --> 00:14:55,853
From "the street"?

217
00:14:55,936 --> 00:14:56,770
[group chuckling]

218
00:14:56,854 --> 00:14:58,606
[Brandon]
No, we went past the crime scene.

219
00:14:58,689 --> 00:15:01,734
There was a lot of blood.
I bet it was Matthew.

220
00:15:01,817 --> 00:15:04,820
-But why on earth would Matthew--?
-Sherry's blog. They're hiding.

221
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:06,780
Matthew is insane.

222
00:15:06,864 --> 00:15:09,241
And Ryan reported
on the Natalie investigation.

223
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:12,328
What if Ryan was asking
too many questions?

224
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:15,122
Hey, hey, heads up!
Fifty grand coming through.

225
00:15:15,205 --> 00:15:16,957
-Not a fan?
-He's my ex.

226
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:20,586
[Brandon] What if the only way
to hide the truth was to murder him?

227
00:15:20,669 --> 00:15:23,839
The library fundraiser's coming up.
My boss asked me to work late.

228
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:25,382
Yeah. He's a gem.

229
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:28,802
He never complains
when I ask him to stay and lock up.

230
00:15:33,557 --> 00:15:35,476
[Kiki] Not up to your standards?

231
00:15:37,811 --> 00:15:38,729
[Love] Yeah.

232
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:41,440
Can't all be winners.

233
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:45,736
Hey, can you make
two dozen bloody-looking ones by tonight?

234
00:15:45,819 --> 00:15:48,614
I'm having my true-crime book club
over to dish.

235
00:15:48,697 --> 00:15:49,531
Yeah, sure.

236
00:15:50,282 --> 00:15:54,870
What's your theory?
I think, his ex, Marienne Bellamy, right?

237
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:57,498
My lawyer friend said
that they were in a custody fight,

238
00:15:57,581 --> 00:16:00,417
and she seems off, you know?

239
00:16:01,168 --> 00:16:04,129
Her ex becomes all successful
and then when she wants him back,

240
00:16:04,213 --> 00:16:06,882
she can't
and it's, like, crime of passion.

241
00:16:08,258 --> 00:16:09,551
What do you think?

242
00:16:10,886 --> 00:16:13,430
You're all scandal-hungry crows
and no amount of feasting

243
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:16,350
on other people's sorrows is gonna
make your lives less hollow.

244
00:16:23,565 --> 00:16:24,400
I'm sorry.

245
00:16:26,443 --> 00:16:27,653
PMS.

246
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:29,238
Right.

247
00:16:30,864 --> 00:16:33,826
-I'll have those cupcakes for you.
-Great. Thank you.

248
00:16:35,035 --> 00:16:36,203
Hey, guys.

249
00:16:36,286 --> 00:16:37,121
Hi.

250
00:16:39,415 --> 00:16:41,250
Get away from me!

251
