773
00:51:53,276 --> 00:51:54,569
[dramatic music playing]

774
00:52:18,135 --> 00:52:19,594
[fire alarm beeping]

775
00:52:21,596 --> 00:52:23,014
[siren waling]

776
00:52:25,517 --> 00:52:27,227
[Joe] In the end, it worked.

777
00:52:27,310 --> 00:52:30,147
There was just enough
half-charred evidence to tell the tale,

778
00:52:30,230 --> 00:52:33,400
including the remains of two human toes,
which were DNA tested.

779
00:52:33,483 --> 00:52:35,652
RIP, me.

780
00:52:35,735 --> 00:52:38,905
Love's farewell filled out details
a burned-out crime scene couldn't.

781
00:52:38,989 --> 00:52:41,575
The rest of Joe Goldberg's body
was never found,

782
00:52:41,658 --> 00:52:44,286
but it was presumed butchered or worse.

783
00:52:45,078 --> 00:52:47,998
Love Quinn became
the Mrs. Lovett of Madre Linda.

784
00:52:48,081 --> 00:52:50,792
Once the nausea passed,
people were ravenous for her.

785
00:52:50,876 --> 00:52:52,419
Her tragic family history,

786
00:52:52,502 --> 00:52:55,297
her quasi-feminist revolt
against upper-class hypocrisy.

787
00:52:55,380 --> 00:52:58,008
A bit of a folk hero,

788
00:52:58,091 --> 00:53:01,887
more famous even than Guinevere Beck.

789
00:53:21,406 --> 00:53:24,075
[Joe] And without my family
poisoning the well...

790
00:53:25,535 --> 00:53:27,412
Madre Linda began to heal.

791
00:53:27,495 --> 00:53:28,496
Beep, beep.

792
00:53:28,580 --> 00:53:29,414
Hey.

793
00:53:30,248 --> 00:53:31,541
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

794
00:53:32,334 --> 00:53:34,085
-How'd it go?
-Oh, you know.

795
00:53:34,169 --> 00:53:38,506
Killed physical therapy, walked 75 yards,

796
00:53:38,590 --> 00:53:40,508
did some intermittent dancing.

797
00:53:41,384 --> 00:53:42,886
Yeah, we should sign up for a 5K.

798
00:53:42,969 --> 00:53:44,012
-A 5K, huh?
-Yeah.

799
00:53:44,095 --> 00:53:45,680
Okay. I'm in if you're in.

800
00:53:45,764 --> 00:53:46,932
[Theo chuckles]

801
00:53:47,724 --> 00:53:49,476
[both cheering]

802
00:53:52,187 --> 00:53:53,688
Good work, Henry!

803
00:53:53,772 --> 00:53:56,650
[Joe] Henry arrived
into Dante and Lansing's life

804
00:53:56,733 --> 00:53:59,486
with a note expressing my last wish.

805
00:54:00,153 --> 00:54:04,115
That they protect Henry
as if he were their own son.

806
00:54:05,242 --> 00:54:07,786
Nobody says no to a man
who got turned into a pie.

807
00:54:08,662 --> 00:54:10,497
No, it wasn't fair of me,

808
00:54:10,580 --> 00:54:12,874
but it was the right thing for Henry.

809
00:54:13,458 --> 00:54:15,335
After a long legal battle,

810
00:54:15,418 --> 00:54:18,255
Dottie, bereaved and still not sober,

811
00:54:18,338 --> 00:54:21,049
yielded custody to Dante and Lansing.

812
00:54:21,675 --> 00:54:24,386
Someday when he's old enough,
he can read the rest of the note.

813
00:54:25,512 --> 00:54:27,305
But that's between him and me.

814
00:54:30,100 --> 00:54:32,102
Didn't take long for the town to regroup.

815
00:54:32,769 --> 00:54:36,481
Jackson and Andrew took over
the bakery with a winky rebrand,

816
00:54:36,564 --> 00:54:38,066
Well-Behaved Women.

817
00:54:38,149 --> 00:54:41,194
Yelp suggests the scones are just okay.

818
00:54:41,278 --> 00:54:43,405
The Insta-friendly shirts
are the real draw.

819
00:54:44,614 --> 00:54:46,741
Kiki and Brandon struck gold

820
00:54:46,825 --> 00:54:49,244
when Brandon developed
an at-home poison test

821
00:54:49,327 --> 00:54:50,745
and accompanying app,

822
00:54:50,829 --> 00:54:53,498
after which Kiki named their new baby.

823
00:54:54,791 --> 00:54:57,585
Toxi. Their child's name is Toxi.

824
00:54:57,669 --> 00:55:01,548
[Cary] We thought,
instead of being prisoners of the cage,

825
00:55:01,631 --> 00:55:02,966
why not master it?

826
00:55:03,508 --> 00:55:04,884
[crowd cheering]

827
00:55:07,846 --> 00:55:11,891
[Joe] Somehow,
Sherry and Cary made it out alive.

828
00:55:11,975 --> 00:55:15,145
Their first move: use Sherry's blog
to savage Love Quinn

829
00:55:15,228 --> 00:55:17,647
and turn themselves
into the real heroes of the story.

830
00:55:17,731 --> 00:55:20,608
Their next move: write a book, of course.

831
00:55:20,692 --> 00:55:24,863
Caged: A Radical Couple's
Therapy Technique.

832
00:55:27,490 --> 00:55:28,783
As for you,

833
00:55:29,743 --> 00:55:30,660
Marienne,

834
00:55:31,328 --> 00:55:34,914
I looked for you,
but you and Juliette were already gone.

835
00:55:34,998 --> 00:55:37,167
Phone number changed,
no forwarding address.

836
00:55:38,251 --> 00:55:40,128
The end of our story remains unwritten.

837
00:55:41,046 --> 00:55:43,840
Did you pity me
when you read what happened?

838
00:55:43,923 --> 00:55:47,594
Did it erase the fear she planted?
Do you still think about us?

839
00:55:47,677 --> 00:55:50,513
Can't believe how many people left
New York after the pandemic.

840
00:55:50,597 --> 00:55:52,640
Way before that. The election?

841
00:55:52,724 --> 00:55:57,145
[Joe] But I have to believe
our paths are destined to cross again.

842
00:55:57,604 --> 00:55:58,646
[bells ringing]

843
00:56:00,982 --> 00:56:02,776
[suspenseful music playing]

844
00:56:16,664 --> 00:56:20,335
Marriage almost ruined both of us,
but we escaped.

845
00:56:20,418 --> 00:56:23,338
Maybe the scars in our hearts
make them stronger.

846
00:56:23,421 --> 00:56:24,255
[man] Nick!

847
00:56:25,256 --> 00:56:26,091
Nick?

848
00:56:26,174 --> 00:56:27,634
["Poussière" playing]

849
00:56:35,308 --> 00:56:36,559
[bells ringing]

850
00:56:41,815 --> 00:56:44,484
[Joe] All I know, mon amour...

851
00:56:48,613 --> 00:56:50,865
is I'll search the world if I have to.

852
00:56:52,826 --> 00:56:54,786
I will find you.
